@page "/about"
@using BlazorTimeline


<Jumbotron Background="Background.Light">
    <JumbotronTitle>
        @Resources.Lang.HeadingAbout
    </JumbotronTitle>
    <Row>
        @{ #if DEBUG}
        <Column ColumnSize="ColumnSize.Is6.OnDesktop.Is12.OnMobile" TextAlignment="TextAlignment.Start">
            <JumbotronSubtitle TextAlignment="TextAlignment.Center" Background="Background.Dark" TextColor="TextColor.White">
                Business me
            </JumbotronSubtitle>
            <Paragraph>
                With about 8 years, i got my first Computer. Mostly used to play games on it, but with higher classes i used it more often also for homework and presentations.
                As i worked and played more and more on the computer, i got more interessted and started working with the Hardware as well.
                Quite soon, my spare time was full with Soccer and doing computer stuff. Which lead me to the decission to start an Apprenticeship as soon as i'm done with school.
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph>
                So i started my work career with 16 years as an "EDV-Technician". I had a lot of fun, sticking all components together and get the systems up and running.
                Another part of the job was solving issues for our users. Time flies by and so i got other responsibilities and work to do.
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph>
                So i got introduced to:
                <ListGroup Flush="true">
                    <ListGroupItem>
                        <Icon Name="IconName.ChevronRight" /> Sharepoint, which was used as our Intranet Platform
                    </ListGroupItem>
                    <ListGroupItem>
                        <Icon Name="IconName.ChevronRight" /> Microsoft Exchange
                    </ListGroupItem>
                    <ListGroupItem>
                        <Icon Name="IconName.ChevronRight" /> Linux, to maintain our Trac/SVN and our Phonesystem (based on Asterisk)
                    </ListGroupItem>
                </ListGroup>
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph>
                As working in first and second/third-level support isn't easy, I moved from the Helpdesk (about 15 years) to System Administration, where I could focus much better on the topics I'm responsable for.
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph>
                Some organizational changes later, I'm out of the IT department and work together with a few Developers. Which opened my eyes, how cool it is. This is how i got into programming.
                Soon i also got more familiar with PowerApps which was quite like my "Developer Entry Point".
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph>
                After about 3 years, i moved back to IT as Cloud Administrator, responsible for mostly the Microsoft Stack. 
                Also started the C# Developer course the longer the course took, the more i wanted to change my career from Administration to Development.
                As IT isn't really responsible for developing software, i had to search for a new path.
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph>
                Which i found in another department at MED-EL. So now i'm able to develop software, get more into SW-Development and learning new languages.
            </Paragraph>
        </Column>

        <Column ColumnSize="ColumnSize.Is6.OnDesktop.Is12.OnMobile" TextAlignment="TextAlignment.Start">
            <JumbotronSubtitle TextAlignment="TextAlignment.Center" Background="Background.Dark" TextColor="TextColor.White">
                Private me
            </JumbotronSubtitle>
        </Column>
        @{#endif}
        <Column ColumnSize="ColumnSize.Is6.OnDesktop.Is12.OnDesktop">
            <Timeline TitleBgColor="DarkGray"
                      TitleColor="#FFFFFF"
                      TextColor="#F3F3F3"
                      TextBgColor="gray">
                <div align="Left">
                    <TimelineItem Title="@Resources.About._1986Title" Time="02.10.1986">
                        @Resources.About._1986Body
                    </TimelineItem>
                    <TimelineItem Title="@Resources.About._1993Title" Time="1993">
                        @Resources.About._1993Body
                    </TimelineItem>
                    <TimelineItem Title="@Resources.About._1997Title" Time="1997">
                        @Resources.About._1997Body
                    </TimelineItem>
                    <TimelineItem Title="@Resources.About._2001Title" Time="2001">
                        @Resources.About._2001Body
                    </TimelineItem>
                    <TimelineItem Title="@Resources.About._200208Title" Time="01.08.2002">
                        @((MarkupString)Resources.About._200208Body)
                    </TimelineItem>
                    <TimelineItem Title="@Resources.About._200209Title" Time="01.09.2002">
                        @Resources.About._200209Body
                    </TimelineItem>
                    <TimelineItem Title="@Resources.About._200212Title" Time="01.12.2002" ButtonText="MED-EL" Link="https://www.medel.com">
                        @Resources.About._200212Body
                    </TimelineItem>
                    <TimelineItem Title="@Resources.About._2004Title" Time="2004">
